I am a speech-language pathologist who is proud to serve the population that I serve.  I chose this profession because of the impact a speech-language pathologist can make in an individual's life.  Let me explain...My father was in a severe car accident when he was only 35 years old.  He was a very healthy, hard-working individual whose car slid off the road in the pouring down rain on April 26, 1997.  Because of that day, my life was forever changed!  My father had traumatic brain injuries, and several strokes as a result of this car accident.  Our family was devastated when after months of being in a coma we realized he was unable to swallow and unable to communicate with us because of the impact of this incident.  We were so grateful for a team of dedicated speech-language pathologists who worked daily with him and our family in order to give him some sort of independence so that he might be able to enjoy his favorite foods aga! in, and so that he might communicate with us his wants, needs, and desires.  After months of hard work, I'm happy to say that my father did indeed regain his ability to eat his favorite foods, and was able to communicate with us.  For us, even though physically he would not do everything he could prior to the car accident, we had my dad and were so grateful that he was able to communicate and able to still tell us "I love you."  Because I saw the impact speech therapy services can have on an individual and on a family, I chose the profession of speech-language pathology because I'm able to give back to others in the same way others gave of themselves for my family.
