This email is in regard to the upcoming vote on the newly revised, proposed House Appropriations Subcommittee Health and Human Services budget released June 2, 2009.  Please VOTE NO to Budget Reductions/Program Eliminations that DECIMATE Speech Therapy/Audiology benefits for NC's children and adults. EPSDT makes this illegal for children.

As outpatient Speech Therapy providers at Wilson Medical Center, we know that these cuts would have a devastating impact on pediatric and adult clients within our community. We provide articulation, language, and cognitive retraining for children in our community. Many of these children would be unable to communicate basic needs/ideas without speech therapy intervention. Many of these children have diagnoses which require ongoing intensive intervention (i.e., Autism, Cerebral Palsy, Down's Syndrome, Closed head injury, Apraxia of speech, dysphagia). If speech therapy services are reduced, these children will enter school with poor communication and comprehension skills placing them at higher risk of failing grade levels and making them more likely to not complete their high school education.

We also provide communication, cognitive, and swallowing intervention for adults who have suffered stroke, traumatic brain injury, aneurysm,  head and neck cancer, and anoxic brain injuries. Speech therapy intervention for these patients is critical to rehabilitate their ability to understand and communicate with others within their homes, communities, and within society (return to work force). Many of these patients are unable to swallow without food and liquids entering the airway and require feeding tubes. Our goal is to return these patients to eating and drinking safely for removal of the feeding tube. These services are critical in facilitating the patient's community re-entry and return to the work force.

We understand that there is a serious budget crisis in our state; however, rate reductions and program reductions will harm local families, local businesses, and the local economy (tax base). Please VOTE NO to Decimation of SLP/Audiology services.

